Document Processing System (AI-Powered)
- A full-stack AI document processing pipeline that supports:
    - File Upload
    - OCR + Classification
    - Data Extraction
    - Validation & Warnings
    - Smart Dashboard (Analytics)
    - MongoDB Atlas storage

This project contains:
- Node.js Backend → Uploads files, calls Python service, stores results in MongoDB, broadcasts notifications
- Python FastAPI Service → OCR, classification, extraction, validation
- Dashboard API → Analytics
- MongoDB Atlas → Stores processed document metadata


POST /api/documents/upload
    - Uploads a document file to the server.
    - https://prnt.sc/gJCjuyn2yZ04

POST /api/documents/classify
    - Uploads a document file and returns the predicted document type (e.g., invoice, receipt, contract).
    - https://prnt.sc/Q31rsBKutD1Q
    -

POST /api/documents/analyze
    - Uploads a document and performs analysis such as text extraction, OCR, or structure detection.
    - https://prnt.sc/0ZCga-hmBtBF

POST /api/documents/extract
    - Extracts key information from a document (e.g., totals, dates, fields).
    - https://prnt.sc/UyAAadal_NYz


Document Processing System - Setup Guide


Run:
Clone the repository
cd document-processing-system

Start the Python OCR Service

Go to folder:
document-processing-system\python-services

Run the virtual environment:
..venv\Scripts\activate

Start the FastAPI server:
python -m uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000

The Python service will run at:
http://localhost:8000

http://localhost:8000/docs

Start the Backend (Node.js)

Go to folder:
document-processing-system\backend

Start the server:
node server.js

The backend will run at:
http://localhost:5000

Start the Frontend (React App)

Go to folder:
document-processing-system\frontend

If first time:
npm install

Start React:
npm start

The frontend will run at:
http://localhost:3000

System Overview

Frontend (React) on port 3000
Backend (Node.js) on port 5000
Python Processing Service (FastAPI) on port 8000

All three must be running at the same time.